paul brings the elders from the athena city and gathers them to give supposedely his last sermon

today's passage was the strongest feeling of this whole week. 

he knows himself very well. he is aware of what will happen and he is intelligent. he shows that hes not blindley going into these places with his oppositions risking it all. To him, it is a necessity to complete his connection with jesus and god. its his life's dedication to spread the gospel of jesus. he knows to his bones that he served the lord with "all humility and with tears and with trials" he is very self-aware of what he has achieved throughout his journey. he tells the elders of this with humility (he has visited house from house by himself in order to manually spread the gospel) and authority (his followers have witnessed him doing this himself) yet his words dont feel demanding -- it feels like he is saying these things truly for our good. 

paul shows incredible dedication to his mission to spread the gospel and that his determination to complete his mission
goes beyond the value of his life. he is not only shows humility and authority he is showing that he is willing to sacrifice
his own life if it meant spreading his words to others just as jesus did: giving life to so many others by sacrificing 
his life for it. 

this weeks passages have taught me that i still have a lot to learn but i wasnt completely sure how much i needed to learn. reading this made me realize that i must live for something greater because true belief not only create people like paul who dedicates his literal life to spreading the words of jesus but doing it in his way -- inspiring others showing humility as well as authority undoubtebly making people excited to follow jesus and mourn his sacrifice. 

i cannot even say that i can live like paul or live to be like paul. however, i thank god for giving me the opportunity to read this passage to learn about paul and how great of a person he was and how a human can achieve greatness with faith and love for god. it gives people purpose, it changes people matures people for the betterment of the entire community. 

we know from previous passages that he has gone through many countries to arrive here. 

i thought this was him bragging his achievements at first but it was moreso about leaving a message inspiring enough for his followers to do the same. 

